  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RPI_SPIDataRW</refname>
    <refpurpose>Function to perform simultaneous read-write on SPI</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   RPI_SPIDataRW(channel,data,len)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>channel:</term>
      <listitem><para> channel number, 0 or 1</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>data   :</term>
      <listitem><para> data to write as list of integers</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>len    :</term>
      <listitem><para> length of the data</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This performs a simultaneous write/read transaction over the selected SPI bus. Data that was in your buffer is overwritten by data returned from the SPI bus.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
RPI_SPIDataRW(0,[13,58],2)
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

